			<h2>Children and Youth with Special Health Care Needs (CYSHCN)</h2>
			<p><img src="../images/CYSHCN.jpg" width="300" height="200" alt="Diverse Kids" class="right border">Maternal and Child Health (MCH) and Children and Youth with Special Health Care Needs (CYSHCN) programs contain similar core public health functions for children and families including resource development, capacity and systems building, and population-based functions such as public information and education, knowledge development,  technical assistance to communities as well as provider training. This  page  contains targeted learning opportunities and resources for professionals who work with CYSHCN and their families.    </p>
